abstract: “It was 30 years ago,’’ Diana Taylor said. “Get over it.”
snippet: “It was 30 years ago,’’ Diana Taylor said. “Get over it.”
lead_paragraph: Diana Taylor, the longtime partner of Michael Bloomberg, this week defended the presidential candidate’s use of nondisclosure agreements, telling those who may be bothered by them: “It was 30 years ago. Get over it.”

abstract: Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
snippet: Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
headline_main: Can Bernie Be Stopped? Some Democratic Donors Are Trying
headline_print_headline: Can Bernie Be Stopped? Some Democratic Donors Are Trying

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders has widened his lead for the Democratic presidential nomination and overtaken Joe Biden in support among African Americans - a voting bloc that until now has largely favored the former vice president, according to a Reuters/Ipsos national poll released on Tuesday.
headline_main: Sanders Surpasses Biden Among African American Voters: Reuters/Ipsos Poll
